@{
    ViewData["Title"] = "4.4 Italicize Text with Emphasis";
}

<div class="container">
    <h1>@ViewData["Title"]</h1>

    <p>To italicize text, thereby placing emphasis on it, we'll use the <code>&lt;em&gt;</code> inline-level element. As with the elements for bold text, there are two different elements that will italicize text, each with a slightly different semantic meaning.</p>

    <p>The <code>&lt;em&gt;</code> element is used semantically to place a stressed emphasis on text; it is thus the most popular option for italicizing text. The other option, the <code>&lt;i&gt;</code> element, is used semantically to convey text in an alternative voice or tone, almost as if it were placed in quotation marks. Again, we will need to gauge the significance of the text we want to italicize and choose an element accordingly.</p>

    <div class="code-container">
        <div class="code-header">HTML Example</div>
        <div class="code-content">
<pre><code class="language-html">
&lt;!-- Stressed emphasis --&gt;
&lt;p&gt;I &lt;em&gt;love&lt;/em&gt; Chicago!&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;!-- Alternative voice or tone --&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The name &lt;i&gt;Shay&lt;/i&gt; means a gift.&lt;/p&gt;
</code></pre>
        </div>
    </div>

    <div class="code-container">
        <div class="code-header">Result</div>
        <div class="code-content result-preview">
            <p>I <em>love</em> Chicago!</p>
            <p>The name <i>Shay</i> means a gift.</p>
        </div>
    </div>

    <p class="mt-4"><strong>Figure 4:</strong> Italicize demo</p>

    <p>These text-level elements are quite handy for bringing our content to life. In addition to these, there are structurally based elements. Whereas text-based elements identify headings and paragraphs, structural elements identify groupings of content such as headers, articles, footers, and so forth. Let's take a look.</p>

    <div class="navigation-buttons">
        <a href="@Url.Action("BoldItalicText", "Frontend")" class="btn btn-outline-primary">← Bold Text</a>
        <a href="@Url.Action("StructureElements", "Frontend")" class="btn btn-primary">Structure Elements →</a>
    </div>
</div>

